# convert user_type, and member_gender into ordered categorical types
ordinal_var_dict = {'user_type': ['Subscriber','Customer'],
                    'member_gender': ['Male', 'Female', 'Other']}

for var in ordinal_var_dict:
    pd_ver = pd.__version__.split(".")
    if (int(pd_ver[0]) > 0) or (int(pd_ver[1]) >= 21):
        ordered_var = pd.api.types.CategoricalDtype(ordered = True,
                                                    categories = ordinal_var_dict[var])
        df_clean[var] = df_clean[var].astype(ordered_var)
    else: #
        df_clean[var] = df_clean[var].astype('category', ordered = True,
                                             categories = ordinal_var_dict[var])
